# ESP32-CAM Browser Viewer (No Storage)

This project captures real-time JPEG images using ESP32-CAM and streams them directly to a browser. No SD card or image storage required.

## üì¶ Hardware
- ESP32-CAM AI-Thinker Module
- FTDI USB-to-Serial Adapter
- Breadboard, jumpers (for flashing)

## üß∞ Software Requirements
- Arduino IDE (v1.8+)
- ESP32 Board URL: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
- Board: "AI Thinker ESP32-CAM"
- Library: Built-in ESP32 Camera library

## ‚öôÔ∏è How to Use
1. Open `ESP32_Cam_WebViewer.ino` in Arduino IDE.
2. Update your Wi-Fi `ssid` and `password`.
3. Select Board: **AI Thinker ESP32-CAM**
4. Upload the code using FTDI adapter (GPIO0 to GND for flashing).
5. Open Serial Monitor.
6. On success, access: `http://<your-device-ip>/` in browser.
7. View live image each time page is refreshed.

‚úÖ No SD Card needed  
‚úÖ Works over Wi-Fi  
‚úÖ Minimal footprint
